<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-25T08:25:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-25T08:25:00-05:00" n="667" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d667">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">484.11 Young, Reuben S., No. 2/16:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Southard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Addis
                                            Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-25T16:00:00+02:35">August 25, 1934—4
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 25—12:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>11. Ethiopian Government offers 2000 Ethiopian dollars in full
                                settlement Doctor Young’s claim account of illegal arrest and will
                                punish Bashawarad.<note n="39" xml:id="d667fn39">Ato Bashawarad
                                    Hapte Wolde, Director of the Municipality of Diré-Daoua.</note>
                                This seems to me reasonable offer. Shall I accept?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Southard</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>